  "title": "Transition-Centric Adaptive Reasoning: ASRA Phase 1 for Interactive Environments",
  "abstract": "ASRA Phase 1 is a minimal agent architecture for fluid reasoning in sequential grid worlds where action labels are latent and environment rules are hidden. The agent maintains transition evidence, infers state-conditioned action semantics, and explores under uncertainty. Version 2 extends the baseline with execution-fidelity theory and competition-scale orchestration concepts.",
